# shadcn/ui Components (apps/web)

Project uses `@shadcn/ui` in `apps/web`. Components are accessible, customizable, and co-located in `src/components/ui`.

## Where components live

Components live in `apps/web/src/components/ui` following aliases in `apps/web/components.json`.

## Using a component

Import via `@/` alias:

```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Tabs, TabsContent, TabsList, TabsTrigger } from '@/components/ui/tabs';
import {
  Card,
  CardContent,
  CardDescription,
  CardFooter,
  CardHeader,
  CardTitle,
} from '@/components/ui/card';
```

Example usage:

```tsx
<Button variant="outline">Click me</Button>

<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Card Description</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <p>Card Content</p>
  </CardContent>
  <CardFooter>
    <p>Card Footer</p>
  </CardFooter>
</Card>
```

## Installing additional components

More components are available at `https://ui.shadcn.com`. Install with the CLI from `apps/web`:

```bash
cd apps/web && npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

Example, to add `accordion`:

```bash
cd apps/web && npx shadcn@latest add accordion
```

Note: `npx shadcn-ui@latest` is deprecated; use `npx shadcn@latest`.

